content.detailedDescription:
I was in the united states army, 4th of the 6th infantry berlin brigade.  also a nato commando.  i was in vicenze on an irf, ( immediate reaction force ) mission.  on perimiter guard on a hill over lookiing vicenza italy.  it was approxamately midnight.  a friend and i were on the same guard watch.  we decided to have a look over the side of the hill we were on to look down on the city of vicenze italy.  as we approached the edge, we noticed a massive object in the sky over the city.  it was , like i said, a tequila sunrise color.  it glowed and made no sound.  by the time we recovered and looked back up,  our full 4 hour guard shift was over.  we had no explanation for it and were punished with an article 13, a usual punishment for leaving post at the time.  we never spoke of it again.   this isn't the only incident i've experienced .  i have had many before and after this.  but what is odd is that since that particular incident i have had what i call a perpetual de ja vou.  it's very eerie.  i don't sleep well , i feel the need to stay conscious to protect my family.
sincerely
brian k conrad
content.summary: Italy , 1978, bright tequila sunrise color.  no sound no emissions, lost 4 hours time.

he said look, pointing to the sky, there are two things flying. when i finally was able to focus at the direction he was point too, i notice something moving quiet fast. my husband said, there are two of them. at this point i am trying to keep my eyes on this "thing" which was moving so fast i could keep up. i told him, i only see one. my husband said, he saw two at first. we are now both trying to keep up with the speed of this object. january 1st, was a clear day. the sun was bright and there were no clouds. one thing that was very clear was the speed, at times it would just disappear by accesding into the clouds. then it reapear and continue moving very fast. we noticed that at all times it was reflecting the sun light. it seem to have metalic shine to it. again it would disappear and then become visible. at one point we noticed that it was just stationary. we made this accessment because we had a point of reference. a black window building on the otherside, maybe a couple of blocks futher down. it just seem to howver and then it just vanished. we kept looking for it, as you would do when you are following the path of an airplane as it passes by. my husband said that when he first noticed it, what caught his attention was the helicopter that was flying by and then noticing two objects that were higher than the helicopter. my husband explained to me that when he first notice the object/s, it seem like out of one it became two, and then they went their separe ways. i only saw one. this object paths was heading towards the glendale mountains, as if were flying towards "cast away restaurant." finally we just lost all sight of it. we are not sure what it was, but by the defenition of and ufo to us this was just that.

content.detailedDescription:
In mid april of 2006, i was sitting in my backyard watching my children play.  i was also looking at the sky because the clouds were particularly beautiful that day.  they were moving across the sky rather fast since it was a windy day, and they had dark bottoms and white billowy tops.  i noticed these 2 large clouds, larger than any of the others in the sky going by, and out of the front of the one closest to me i saw a sort of cigar shaped object come completely out of it as if it accidently sped up.  it then slowed down to a complete stop and went back into the cloud in reverse as if who ever was piloting it realized it over shot the cloud and was out in the wide open.
 
the object appeared to be at least 3 times larger than a huge airplane like a boeing 747.  it had around 50 to 100 large windows in 2 rows, one above the other, running along the center axis going down the side of it.  the skin of the object had a metallic color, and i could actually see the sun light glittering on it as well as seeing the reflection of the sun in its windows.  i had a little less than about 3 seconds to see the object, but in that time i was able to see it in enough detail to know that the front of it looked exactly like the back of it, and it didn���t have any wings on it or a carriage underneath of it like a blimp would.  also, it made no noise.
 
the one thing that i can say for sure is that it was not anything i���ve ever seen.  i don���t think it was of this world.  let me also say that this was a life changing experience for me because prior to seeing it, i thought that there was life in the universe, but most likely it didn���t make it to earth yet.  now, i believe the earth is being visited.

content.detailedDescription:
I took my little dog out for a walk late, i like to look at the stars as i am in the country.  while at the end of my driveway i looked north, up the highway and saw a large narrow object hovering but as i watched, it was really moving very, very slowly just above the tree tops. i looked and my dog was not noticing it at all, no reaction as there was no noise.  i am hear of hearing for high pitch but the dog was not interested so i say no noise at all.  i kept thinking i should hear a hum, with it up in the air with no wings or propellers.  

it was a narrow rectangle shape. gray, with a small redish lighted done on top and a amber small light. across the area i was looking at were 3 or 4, i am not sure of number now as i was more impressed with the big round cicle white lights, that i thought of as engines or something, there were no flames, or waves of air, that i could tell but they were the whitest white i have ever seen...I am an artisan and now no lights or color white look white to me but rather have a dull yellow or amber tint.  the large white circles were also next to an area that seemed to be black vertical bars or vents on about a third of the entire rectangular area to the left. the lights on top had low ilregular flashes within them, nothing like the lights on planes. no light projected in any fashion on to road or trees.

i did not feel fear, just wander and curious, i could see the sky around it, sides and below.  i tired to judge the size and posistion by the tree tops, width of the two lane highway and it's dirrection of movement.  it seemed to be as wide as the highway it not a bit more, even as high as the pine tree it was close to.  there was no wind movement of the tree as it crossed over them. i just stood there and watched it, as i figured to run in and get the camera, it would be gone; also to get my car keys to follow i figured the same.  

after it reached the forrest edge on my left side, i just walked slowly toward my house, trying to figure if the afbase to the southeast of me might have any hoover craft, trying to think of what it could have been, when i hear a deep rumble rather like the trains sometime have but it was a short sound then total quiet again. 

i went in and just went to bed, i guess i was in wonder or shock, and then the next day or two, there was an unusal amount of jet flights and even for two nights helochopers with bright green and red lights on their runners that didn't blink flying around my area. two days after i looked online for a place to report it and could not get any of the links with mufon of ga to work so told my son, who lives above atlanta, about it.  he is the only one i have talked to about it, i am a mature adult and have only seen one other thing when i lived in north ga which was a white ball like a star take a 45 degree turn in the night sky, my younger son was with me then.

i'm still haveing trouble finding the right box in my mind to put this, as i can not relate any thing i know to it.  that is other than science fiction and this thing was real !!!!  i still feel no fear to walk my dog and watch the sky but man, what was it ???

after the ufo landed across the way from us, it continued to change from orange/yellow burning sun to bright bright light and  we started to worry it would start a fire in the dry grass it had landed on, although 
each time it became a bright light or orange sun you could see the outline  or shadows of the oak trees in that were in between us and  of the ufo.
we continued to watch the ufo until about 11p then i became very very sleepy, then my brother turns to me and tells me he can hardly keep his eyes open either so we go to bed���awaken at day break to the sound of jet engines to find the air force and army choppers, there were military jeeps and men and others in same place we watched the ufo land the night before. but i couldn���t seem to care or get excited about all the actions caused by the ufo landing quite the opposite of who i really am!! completely unnatural reaction for me!

content.detailedDescription: My mom, sister and myself were watching t.V. when we heard a low but distinct hum. thinking it was the goodyear blimp, my sister and i looked out of the back window of our home only to see a u.F.O rotating very slowly above our house and moving in a straight line over our neighborhood. it was very low as if i could hit it with a rock. we yelled for our mother to come over to see it but she thought we were making it up. my sister and i watched the bright lights of blues, reds and greens flicker and spin on the bottom of the craft. the object itself was dark but because of the illumination we could see that it was as big as four houses. we were not scared but facinated as we watched it glide past the horizon. to this day we still share this memory. about 20 years later i was talking to a friend who grew up in the same neighborhood and when i told him about the experience we had had, he went flush because after narrowing down the time frame he too had experienced something that he had not shared with anyone. he states that that exact same night, some sort of tiny, hairless creature had apparated into his room, scared the mess out of him then disappeared. i know this sounds like a story but i have witnesses. i swear that this is true!

the ufo was silent except for the sound of the wind it created which pulled moms dress and the clothes on the clothes line toward the craft.
after a few minutes, the ufo began to rise back up to the sky about 300 ft where it began to wobble in flight then the ufo began to wobble and descend again, the ufo dropped out of site behind the nearby mountain ridge, then there was an explosion and a fire and shortly after that, the forestry dept. made us evacuate. 
this was the beginning of a life long visits from ufo`s on our family. my mother brothers report sighting ufo too.

content.detailedDescription:
On thursday, october 9, 2009 at approximately 8:40 p.M. central time, i took our dogs outside. as i was standing on the east side of the house having a cigarette, i noticed a lighted odject in the sky to the southeast. the sky was overcast this night, but the object was below the clouds and appeared to be heading in my direction. it appeared to be at a height of a couple thousand feet. we are on a flight path for o'hare airport so there are planes going over all of the time. at first i thought that it was a plane as one had just passed by a minute, or so earlier, but something about this object didn't look right. i realized then that it was the lights. a plane generally has four lights that you can see; one on each wing tip, one near the nose, and one near the tail. the wing lights are usually one blue light, and one red light that blink constantly. the remaining two lights are white. this object had six lights, three on each of two sides that formed a horizontal, or vertical row. there were two red lights on each side, one at each end and one white light in the middle on each side. the lights shined constantly at the same brightness, they did not blink/flash at all. the object came from the southeast in a slow, but steady pace. i watched it for approximately two, or three minutes, then went into the house and told my brother to come out and see this thing.
  we returned outside at approximately 8:45 p.M. i pointed the object out to him and we continued to watch it unobstructed. at this time, the object now changed direction and headed straight west, but when it changed direction it didn't bank, or turn like a plane would. it just seemed to "float" in that direction. we could clearly see the six lights and the two sides that formed an upward v. we could hear no sound of any kind coming from the object.It appeared to remain at the same height. as we watched, the object continued west and followed the course of a creek that flows about 100 yards to the south of our house. we still had a clear, unobstructed view of the object. the object followed the creek until it was approximately even with our house at which time it once more changed direction, and began to "float" to the northwest. it came across the cornfield, and the houses across the street and passed overhead just to the west of our house. we watched as it floated by overhead. when it got past our garage we could now see that it had three sides instead of two and each side had the same two red and one white lights. with the dark sky background we couldn't tell if the object was solid in the center, or not. it still made no sound as it floated overhead, no engine noise, no hot-air furnace like a hot-air balloon would have. it was completely silent. i asked my brother if he could hear any kind of sound coming from it and he said no. we watched as it continued to float to the northwest and out of sight. the whole episode probably lasted nine, or ten minutes from start to finish. another plane came by just after the object disappeared from our sight.
content.summary: Saw something, not a plane or a hot-air balloon.
